content.text: Measuring tasks using iCloud Private Relay

inlineContent.text: iCloud Private Relay can change the timing and sequence of events for your tasks by sending requests through a set of privacy proxies. All tasks that use iCloud Private Relay set the
property in their transaction metrics. In this case, the
property contains the address of the proxy, and not the origin server.

If the connection is encrypted, the user agent starts a TLS security handshake to secure the connection. After the connection to the server is established, the user agent requests the specified resource, and receives a response.
